725858f-c.text:
138th Street, east side, north of Ninetieth to Jamaica Aves. (elevated line thereon), showing in a set of four'views the C. Carl house of 1860. J.M. McCauley was the owner in 1873; and Wm. Danmar from 1902 to 1934. This house was erected by a member of the Royal Scotch Stuart family about 1780. The walls of this house are twentytwo inches thick filled with brick; the shutters outside and inside were barricaded with iron bars. A wing detached, once a part of this house, situated in rear thereof, was used as a carpenter shop. It
was demolished on April 5, 1934.
1923.
View 2: April 1923.
View 3: 1922.
View 4: April 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
